1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
 On the very first day of seminary, I met Laughing Jesus.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,040
 He was hanging awkwardly on the side

3
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:10,560
 of a cluttered cork notice board,

4
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:12,500
 surrounded by handwritten notices,

5
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:16,200
 trying to sell textbooks and rusted bicycles.

6
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:19,480
 I sat next to Laughing Jesus for about an hour and a half

7
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:21,560
 before I even realized he was there.

8
00:00:21,560 --> 00:00:23,720
 I can be a little bit like that with Jesus.

9
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:30,760
 Laughing Jesus was this pencil drawing of Jesus,

10
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:35,140
 the kind of drawing I had never encountered before.

11
00:00:35,140 --> 00:00:36,960
 In fact, I wanna show you the exact drawing.

12
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:38,500
 It was that one there.

13
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:42,960
 Now, undoubtedly, this was Jesus.

14
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:44,640
 I mean, it looked like Jesus, right?

15
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,520
 I mean, he's got that unkempt beard.

16
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:48,280
 He's got the kind of long, flowing hair.

17
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:49,860
 He's a little bit more Middle Eastern looking

18
00:00:49,860 --> 00:00:51,480
 than I was used to, but I was at seminary,

19
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:53,440
 so there you go.

20
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:56,080
 It wasn't actually kinda how he looked

21
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:57,360
 that kinda caught my eye.

22
00:00:57,360 --> 00:01:00,540
 It was what he was doing that caught my eye.

23
00:01:00,540 --> 00:01:05,540
 Jesus was laughing, and not just kinda like,

24
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:07,840
 oh, that's kind of a nice antidote.

25
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:10,120
 He's like laughing, laughing, right?

26
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,880
 Like either Jesus has just told a great joke

27
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:14,400
 to the disciples, and he's like,

28
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,240
 (laughing)

29
00:01:15,240 --> 00:01:17,000
 you're like that to them,

30
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,880
 or maybe someone's told Jesus a great joke,

31
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:22,840
 and he's laughing alongside of them with that great joke.

32
00:01:22,840 --> 00:01:24,960
 And as I stared at this, as I was sitting there

33
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:27,520
 in my first class at seminary on the very first day,

34
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:31,360
 I felt an emotion rising up inside of me,

35
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:34,280
 an emotion towards Jesus I had not felt before,

36
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:37,080
 and after a while, I was able to name that emotion.

37
00:01:37,080 --> 00:01:39,740
 Laughing Jesus offended me.

38
00:01:39,740 --> 00:01:42,900
 He offended me.

39
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:46,360
 Because as I looked at that picture,

40
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:49,480
 I noticed that the artist had captured Jesus

41
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:52,020
 in a misrepresented way.

42
00:01:52,860 --> 00:01:55,900
 Because the Jesus I knew was far too serious

43
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:57,540
 to laugh like that.

44
00:01:57,540 --> 00:02:00,940
 The Jesus I knew was here on earth

45
00:02:00,940 --> 00:02:03,640
 doing a very sober mission,

46
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:06,500
 where he had come to heal people who were blind,

47
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:07,740
 to cast out demons.

48
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:10,700
 He had come to listen and obey his father.

49
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:12,860
 He had come to teach the things he needed to teach.

50
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:15,180
 He had come to be obedient to death.

51
00:02:15,180 --> 00:02:17,580
 Jesus was not laughing about any of that.

52
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:18,420
 No sirree.

53
00:02:18,420 --> 00:02:21,440
 As I looked at this more and more,

54
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:26,060
 I was like, this is not the Jesus that I understand.

55
00:02:26,060 --> 00:02:27,360
 I thought about all the jokes

56
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,860
 that would make me laugh like this,

57
00:02:28,860 --> 00:02:30,860
 and I realized none of them were holy.

58
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:34,780
 Are you with me, church?

59
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:38,340
 And I realized that this is a Jesus

60
00:02:38,340 --> 00:02:41,820
 that didn't fit the frameworks for Jesus that I had.

61
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:46,820
 Not the pious, divine, sitting on the throne kind of Jesus

62
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:49,480
 that I had met when I was a youth.

63
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:53,120
 Not the powerful, sovereign, almighty Jesus

64
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,460
 that I had followed in my 20s.

65
00:02:55,460 --> 00:02:59,420
 This was certainly not the more chilled out, calm, relaxed,

66
00:02:59,420 --> 00:03:03,540
 justice loving Jesus that I had followed in my 30s.

67
00:03:03,540 --> 00:03:05,980
 The reality was laughing Jesus

68
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:09,180
 was simply a Jesus I didn't know.

69
00:03:09,180 --> 00:03:11,500
 Now I don't know about you,

70
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:14,620
 but as Christians when we're encountered

71
00:03:14,620 --> 00:03:17,340
 by a version of Jesus that we don't know,

72
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:21,120
 we tend to as Christians have a default towards skepticism.

73
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:25,140
 Now on the one side, there's a healthiness to that.

74
00:03:25,140 --> 00:03:29,100
 Oftentimes yesterday's skepticism is today's wisdom.

75
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,500
 But I think there's a worrying trend

76
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:32,980
 that we have in the church.

77
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:35,880
 That when we see something new of Jesus,

78
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:38,460
 or we hear about something new of Jesus,

79
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:39,820
 we kind of have that reaction

80
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:41,700
 like I had on the first day of seminary.

81
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,900
 There's skepticism, we draw back,

82
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:45,780
 we're like, this isn't the kind of Jesus

83
00:03:45,780 --> 00:03:47,500
 that I was aware of, and I don't know

84
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,620
 what to do with this Jesus.

85
00:03:49,620 --> 00:03:52,340
 And oftentimes our response is a little bit

86
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:54,520
 like the people in Bethlehem.

87
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:58,420
 I don't think there's room in the inn for that Jesus.

88
00:03:58,420 --> 00:04:02,020
 And as I was looking at this,

89
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:07,020
 I realized one of the reasons why he offended me so much.

90
00:04:07,020 --> 00:04:11,340
 It was because the artist had captured a moment of Jesus

91
00:04:11,340 --> 00:04:14,620
 in his most human-ness.

92
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:16,340
 Now I understood, 'cause I was at seminary,

93
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:18,500
 that the incarnation meant that God was fully God

94
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:19,900
 and fully human at the same time,

95
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:22,220
 that Jesus in this incarnation brought all that together.

96
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:25,580
 I understood theoretically and theologically about that.

97
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:29,260
 But when I was encountered by a moment of his human-ness,

98
00:04:29,260 --> 00:04:30,140
 it annoyed me.

99
00:04:30,140 --> 00:04:33,700
 And it annoyed me because I could see

100
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:35,340
 that the artist was trying to say,

101
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:38,660
 this is also Jesus, the human Jesus,

102
00:04:38,660 --> 00:04:40,420
 the one who's like at a barbecue,

103
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:43,320
 cracking jokes with his buddies.

104
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:46,060
 And I realized that the reason why this offended me

105
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:48,540
 was because that wasn't the Jesus I needed.

106
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:52,980
 I didn't need a Jesus to be a buddy with me at the barbecue.

107
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:55,580
 I needed Jesus to save my soul

108
00:04:55,580 --> 00:04:57,820
 from the brokenness and the sin that I was carrying.

109
00:04:57,820 --> 00:05:00,820
 I needed a Jesus, in other words, that wasn't like me.

110
00:05:00,820 --> 00:05:04,660
 I intentionally needed a Jesus that wasn't like me.

111
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:05,740
 Are you with me?

112
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:08,540
 Like I wanted a Jesus that was different from me

113
00:05:08,540 --> 00:05:10,740
 because I knew who I was.

114
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:14,280
 And I knew that my human-ness meant X, Y, and Z.

115
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:15,960
 I could see the frailties in me,

116
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,540
 the insecurities I carried,

117
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:19,200
 the sin that was so prevalent in me.

118
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:21,300
 I didn't wanna worship a Jesus that was like me.

119
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:23,720
 I wanted to worship a Jesus that was so different from me,

120
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:25,520
 transcendent from my human-ness,

121
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:27,820
 able to rise above those emotions,

122
00:05:27,820 --> 00:05:29,720
 rise above that sin and that brokenness,

123
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,480
 and save me powerfully.

124
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:36,480
 So I had constructed a version of Jesus that I needed.

125
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:39,680
 And when I was encountered with a version of Jesus

126
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,740
 that as much as Him as anything else,

127
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:43,920
 because it's not the one that I needed,

128
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,660
 it was easy for me to reject Him.

129
00:05:45,660 --> 00:05:54,220
 I wanted Jesus to be superhuman, not simply human.

130
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:58,580
 I think one of the main reasons why we fail

131
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:01,600
 to make room in our hearts for more of Jesus

132
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:04,340
 is because the room that we have constructed in our hearts

133
00:06:04,340 --> 00:06:06,620
 fits only the Jesus that we want,

134
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:09,380
 not necessarily the Jesus that is.

135
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:12,640
 The Jesus of our own making,

136
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:15,420
 the Jesus of our own construction,

137
00:06:15,420 --> 00:06:20,020
 the Jesus that fits comfortably to what I need Him to be,

138
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:24,420
 the Jesus that can save what is going on in my life,

139
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:26,420
 the Jesus that feels good to me.

140
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:29,060
 And when Jesus kinda comes to us

141
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:31,020
 and reveals a part of Himself

142
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:33,780
 that we hadn't encountered before,

143
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:37,460
 rather than open ourselves up more for that reality of Jesus,

144
00:06:37,460 --> 00:06:40,340
 we so often shut Him down, push Him out,

145
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:43,300
 and tell Him that there's no room in the end.

146
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:45,620
 The wrestle that we have to do

147
00:06:45,620 --> 00:06:47,940
 is that one of the greatest limitations and barriers

148
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:50,020
 to discipleship for us Christians

149
00:06:50,020 --> 00:06:52,020
 is I think the limitations we place

150
00:06:52,020 --> 00:06:54,540
 on our thinking about Jesus.

151
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:58,220
 And we stay shut away from fresh ways of thinking

152
00:06:58,220 --> 00:07:00,660
 and reflecting and embracing the King of Kings

153
00:07:00,660 --> 00:07:01,860
 and the Lord of Lords.

154
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:03,540
 And so when Jesus shows up

155
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:05,740
 and reveals something that's different

156
00:07:05,740 --> 00:07:08,940
 to the shape that we had created for Him to fit in,

157
00:07:08,940 --> 00:07:11,220
 and we suddenly realize that He doesn't fit anymore

158
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:14,140
 the nice, neat shape that I had created for Him,

159
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:17,180
 rather than change my shape, I change Him.

160
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:19,620
 Come on, church.

161
00:07:19,620 --> 00:07:24,020
 I fit Him into the shape that I've made for Him.

162
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:26,300
 Rather than expand my heart,

163
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:30,180
 I shrink His divinity down to me.

164
00:07:30,180 --> 00:07:34,900
 If we wanna make more room for Jesus,

165
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:38,340
 we must first dethrone the Jesus we make.

166
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:41,620
 Come on, church.

167
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:43,300
 We wanna make more room for Jesus,

168
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:46,580
 we need to first dethrone the Jesus

169
00:07:46,580 --> 00:07:48,460
 that we have constructed,

170
00:07:48,460 --> 00:07:51,420
 the Jesus that fits nice to us,

171
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:55,340
 the Jesus that serves us.

172
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:57,980
 And we need to begin to think and experience

173
00:07:57,980 --> 00:08:01,260
 and encounter the Jesus who really is.

174
00:08:03,140 --> 00:08:05,580
 It is this challenge that Luke,

175
00:08:05,580 --> 00:08:09,020
 in presenting the birth narrative of Jesus,

176
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:11,540
 finishes his Christmas story with.

177
00:08:11,540 --> 00:08:15,220
 He finishes with a story that challenges

178
00:08:15,220 --> 00:08:18,340
 how we come to think about the Messiah.

179
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:20,540
 I wanna read this to you from Luke chapter two.

180
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:22,620
 This is the final chapter, if you will,

181
00:08:22,620 --> 00:08:24,300
 to his Christmas narrative.

182
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:28,340
 And I wanna pick it up in verse 22 of chapter two in Luke.

183
00:08:28,340 --> 00:08:29,980
 When the time of their purification,

184
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:33,340
 according to the law of Moses, had been completed,

185
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:35,020
 Joseph and Mary took him to Jerusalem

186
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:36,740
 to present him before the Lord.

187
00:08:36,740 --> 00:08:39,060
 The time of purification, according to the law of Moses,

188
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,780
 was about 40 days.

189
00:08:40,780 --> 00:08:45,740
 So we reckon here Jesus is about 40 to 45 days old

190
00:08:45,740 --> 00:08:48,100
 as Mary and Joseph bring him to the temple.

191
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:51,100
 As it is written in the law of the Lord,

192
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:54,260
 every firstborn male is to be consecrated to the Lord

193
00:08:54,260 --> 00:08:57,060
 and to offer a sacrifice in keeping with what is said

194
00:08:57,060 --> 00:08:58,460
 in the law of the Lord,

195
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:01,940
 a pair of doves and two young pigeons.

196
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:06,100
 Now, there was a man in Jerusalem called Simeon

197
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:08,180
 who was righteous and devout.

198
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:10,180
 He was waiting for the consolation of Israel

199
00:09:10,180 --> 00:09:12,700
 and the Holy Spirit was upon him.

200
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:14,500
 It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit

201
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:18,060
 that he would not die before he had seen the Lord's Christ.

202
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:20,020
 What a beautiful promise.

203
00:09:20,020 --> 00:09:23,020
 Moved by the Spirit, he went into the temple courts.

204
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:25,500
 And when the parents brought in the child Jesus

205
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:28,660
 to do for him, which was custom to the Lord required,

206
00:09:28,660 --> 00:09:31,340
 Simeon took him in his arms.

207
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:33,740
 I wonder if the parents freaked out about that, by the way.

208
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:35,100
 Like, you know, that's kind of weird.

209
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:36,260
 It's like they're walking in with the baby

210
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:39,180
 and Simeon sweeps the child off of their arms

211
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:41,340
 into his hands, scary kind of moment.

212
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:44,420
 And Simeon took him in his arms and praised God

213
00:09:44,420 --> 00:09:47,780
 by saying this, "Sovereign Lord, as you have promised,

214
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:50,460
 "you can now dismiss your servant in peace.

215
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:52,740
 "For my eyes have seen your salvation,

216
00:09:52,740 --> 00:09:55,100
 "which you have prepared in the sight of all the people,

217
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:59,580
 "a light for revelation to the Gentiles

218
00:09:59,580 --> 00:10:02,500
 "and for the glory of your people, Israel."

219
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:05,300
 The child's father and mother marveled

220
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:07,820
 at what was said about him.

221
00:10:07,820 --> 00:10:09,980
 Yeah, as Luke draws this story to a close,

222
00:10:09,980 --> 00:10:12,980
 he starts by, he's a master storyteller, by the way.

223
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,860
 He starts by telling you a picture

224
00:10:14,860 --> 00:10:18,260
 of this beautiful, pious, religious couple, Mary and Joseph.

225
00:10:18,260 --> 00:10:21,220
 He paints them as religious and devout,

226
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:24,660
 as adhering to all of the Old Testament law

227
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:26,980
 that was responsible and requiring for them

228
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:28,100
 to do the things that they do.

229
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,700
 So he tells you that they go to the temple

230
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:32,700
 on about 40 days of Jesus' birth.

231
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,220
 They've purified themselves,

232
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:36,180
 as was according to the law of Moses.

233
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:38,740
 They then come and do three things in the temple.

234
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:41,300
 The first was a further purification of themselves

235
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:44,020
 by bringing a sacrifice of either a lamb or the doves,

236
00:10:44,020 --> 00:10:45,540
 most likely pigeons for them,

237
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:47,620
 as they were of the poorer class.

238
00:10:47,620 --> 00:10:50,460
 Then they would take Jesus and present him before the priest,

239
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:53,380
 which is what was right to do for a firstborn son.

240
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:55,420
 Then they would offer another sacrifice

241
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:58,780
 as they dedicate their child to the service of the Lord.

242
00:10:58,780 --> 00:11:00,740
 So Luke is presenting to us a story

243
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:02,780
 where this religious and devout couple

244
00:11:02,780 --> 00:11:06,220
 do what was required of them in the Old Testament law.

245
00:11:06,220 --> 00:11:08,780
 He wants you to see that they're adhering

246
00:11:08,780 --> 00:11:10,380
 to all of the scriptures,

247
00:11:10,380 --> 00:11:13,060
 all of the things that have been taught in Moses,

248
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:15,340
 all of the things that the Old Testament had suggested.

249
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:18,180
 Here's Mary and Joseph doing it right.

250
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:21,580
 They are operating within the framework

251
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:24,420
 that they understood at the time.

252
00:11:24,420 --> 00:11:29,020
 And Luke wants you to understand the irony of this.

253
00:11:29,020 --> 00:11:31,860
 It's ironic because the very child

254
00:11:31,860 --> 00:11:35,060
 that they are now dedicating to the service of the Lord

255
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:37,820
 is going to be the one who will grow up

256
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:42,020
 and actually break the box that had been created.

257
00:11:42,020 --> 00:11:45,100
 So here's Mary and Joseph living within this box

258
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:47,100
 of here's how we should do things

259
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,220
 according to the law of Moses.

260
00:11:49,220 --> 00:11:51,380
 And their child, the very one they're dedicating,

261
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:54,420
 is gonna be the one that is gonna inaugurate a new wine

262
00:11:54,420 --> 00:11:56,140
 through a new wineskin.

263
00:11:56,140 --> 00:11:58,340
 One who's gonna bring the kingdom of God,

264
00:11:58,340 --> 00:11:59,820
 who's not gonna abolish that law,

265
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:02,020
 but fulfill it and fulfill it in ways

266
00:12:02,020 --> 00:12:03,660
 that they never expected him to do.

267
00:12:03,660 --> 00:12:04,780
 He's gonna come and say,

268
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:07,940
 "Look, what you're doing on the Sabbath right now is wrong.

269
00:12:07,940 --> 00:12:10,540
 "You're so caught up in the law, you've forgotten grace."

270
00:12:10,540 --> 00:12:12,500
 He's gonna say some pretty strong things

271
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:14,980
 to the rulers and the teachers and the Pharisees of the law.

272
00:12:14,980 --> 00:12:17,460
 He's gonna do stuff where people will stand back and go,

273
00:12:17,460 --> 00:12:19,620
 "No Messiah would ever do this."

274
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:21,180
 And he's gonna stand before the people and say,

275
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:23,460
 "If you've got ears, you're gonna be able to hear.

276
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:25,900
 "If you've got eyes, you're gonna be able to see me."

277
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:28,900
 He's gonna disrupt all of the things

278
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:32,260
 that Mary and Joseph are adhering to so perfectly

279
00:12:32,260 --> 00:12:35,700
 and Luke's like, "Watch what happens next."

280
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:43,140
 And God always, in these moments

281
00:12:43,140 --> 00:12:47,140
 where there's something significant shaping history,

282
00:12:47,140 --> 00:12:50,900
 loves to break in and bring a change.

283
00:12:51,420 --> 00:12:53,900
 And God decides that this is the moment

284
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:57,180
 where he's gonna proclaim something about his son

285
00:12:57,180 --> 00:13:00,140
 publicly before all of Israel.

286
00:13:00,140 --> 00:13:03,020
 And he does so by doing how he always did it

287
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:04,580
 through the Old Testament,

288
00:13:04,580 --> 00:13:07,300
 by filling the spirit into a man

289
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:11,180
 who is a prophet of his people before his people.

290
00:13:11,180 --> 00:13:14,900
 We are introduced to this man by the name of Simeon

291
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:16,620
 in verses 25 and 26.

292
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:19,060
 Notice how Luke describes him.

293
00:13:19,060 --> 00:13:20,060
 It says in verse 25,

294
00:13:20,060 --> 00:13:22,660
 "Now there was a man in Jerusalem called Simeon

295
00:13:22,660 --> 00:13:24,300
 "who was righteous and devout.

296
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:26,780
 "He was waiting for the consolation of Israel

297
00:13:26,780 --> 00:13:28,820
 "and the Holy Spirit was upon him."

298
00:13:28,820 --> 00:13:31,140
 That's a pretty darn good resume, by the way.

299
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:33,180
 "The Holy Spirit was upon him.

300
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:35,220
 "It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit

301
00:13:35,220 --> 00:13:40,140
 "that he would not die before he had seen the Lord's Christ."

302
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:41,500
 Can you imagine what this was like?

303
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,820
 Sometime in Simeon's life,

304
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:44,860
 and we don't know when it happened,

305
00:13:44,860 --> 00:13:47,020
 the Holy Spirit had told him somehow,

306
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:49,100
 maybe through a dream, maybe in another way,

307
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,940
 that he would, with his own eyes,

308
00:13:50,940 --> 00:13:52,980
 see the Messiah for himself.

309
00:13:52,980 --> 00:13:55,900
 You can imagine how exciting that must have been for Simeon.

310
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:58,780
 I'm gonna finally see this longed for.

311
00:13:58,780 --> 00:14:00,660
 Remember, the Jewish people had been praying

312
00:14:00,660 --> 00:14:03,620
 for 400 years up to this point for this coming Messiah,

313
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:05,780
 and the Lord said by his spirit to Simeon,

314
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:07,940
 "You're not gonna die before you see this."

315
00:14:07,940 --> 00:14:09,740
 Now, he was probably quite young at the time.

316
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:11,700
 He's like, "Good, I'm not prepared to die right now.

317
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:13,380
 "That's a good thing."

318
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:15,940
 And maybe every day he went into the temple courts,

319
00:14:15,940 --> 00:14:17,860
 every day scanning the children

320
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:19,820
 that were being brought in for these ceremonies,

321
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:21,500
 which happened every day,

322
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:23,700
 and he's praying and going, "Lord, is it this one?

323
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:24,980
 "Lord, is it that one?

324
00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:26,500
 "Lord, I hope it's not that one."

325
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,340
 And whatever, right?

326
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:30,540
 He's like looking at these kids,

327
00:14:30,540 --> 00:14:32,540
 and he's trying to work out which one is which,

328
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:36,380
 and no Messiah, and so he goes home every day.

329
00:14:36,380 --> 00:14:38,540
 Can you imagine what it would have felt like

330
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:42,420
 to have a promise of the Lord spoken into your spirit,

331
00:14:42,420 --> 00:14:44,900
 holding to that promise, going every day,

332
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:47,540
 believing that that promise is gonna be fulfilled that day,

333
00:14:47,540 --> 00:14:48,820
 and then returning home,

334
00:14:48,820 --> 00:14:52,340
 realizing that the promise hasn't come through.

335
00:14:52,340 --> 00:14:57,780
 And Luke describes him as faithful, devout,

336
00:14:57,780 --> 00:15:00,260
 holding on despite the long wait,

337
00:15:00,260 --> 00:15:01,780
 and we don't know how long that wait is,

338
00:15:01,780 --> 00:15:03,460
 but we know now that he's very old

339
00:15:03,460 --> 00:15:04,740
 because the first thing he says

340
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:05,860
 when the Holy Spirit's thought of,

341
00:15:05,860 --> 00:15:08,100
 he's like, "Oh, finally, I can now die."

342
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:10,140
 (congregation laughing)

343
00:15:10,140 --> 00:15:11,660
 But really what he's saying is

344
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:14,340
 the culmination of the promise has come.

345
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:20,020
 This idea shakes a few things up for us, I think,

346
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:22,540
 because Luke is describing him as faithful and obedient,

347
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:25,340
 and yet the promise hasn't come through yet,

348
00:15:25,340 --> 00:15:27,940
 which I think teaches us a very important lesson,

349
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:29,900
 that faithfulness and obedience to the Lord

350
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,500
 does not mean an easy life.

351
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,340
 It doesn't mean that suddenly

352
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:34,700
 all the answers are gonna come.

353
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:35,980
 It doesn't mean that immediately

354
00:15:35,980 --> 00:15:37,180
 the promise will be revealed.

355
00:15:37,180 --> 00:15:38,660
 It doesn't even mean that the promise

356
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:41,580
 will come through in our timing, in our preference,

357
00:15:41,580 --> 00:15:45,580
 in the nice little neat box that we have created for it.

358
00:15:46,180 --> 00:15:50,140
 Sometimes being faithful and obedient means having to wait.

359
00:15:50,140 --> 00:15:53,340
 And if that encourages you, maybe challenges you,

360
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:55,140
 well, good news, in January,

361
00:15:55,140 --> 00:15:57,740
 we're actually gonna do a whole series on Psalm 27.

362
00:15:57,740 --> 00:15:58,580
 I'm really excited about it.

363
00:15:58,580 --> 00:16:00,700
 We're gonna be talking about this season of waiting

364
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:02,500
 that many of us wrestle with

365
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:05,100
 and what we can learn and encounter in that season.

366
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:07,580
 So I'm not gonna talk more about that now,

367
00:16:07,580 --> 00:16:09,580
 but I wanna say this,

368
00:16:09,580 --> 00:16:12,940
 that it's often in those longer seasons,

369
00:16:12,940 --> 00:16:16,340
 like it was for Simeon, who faithfully every day showed up

370
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:18,060
 and faithfully went home and said,

371
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,500
 "I guess it's gonna be tomorrow."

372
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:21,900
 And he came back the next day and he went home.

373
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:26,060
 And then on this day, everything changed.

374
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:31,060
 So often God breaks in when things are the bleakest,

375
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:35,500
 when they are the darkest, when they are the coldest,

376
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,620
 where it feels like he's the furthest away.

377
00:16:37,620 --> 00:16:39,780
 Sometimes it's when we're in the valley

378
00:16:39,780 --> 00:16:41,260
 of the shadow of death,

379
00:16:41,260 --> 00:16:45,620
 that he shows up, breaks in, brings a word, makes a change.

380
00:16:45,620 --> 00:16:48,100
 And here's a moment for Simeon

381
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:50,180
 where he didn't know it was gonna be this day

382
00:16:50,180 --> 00:16:52,820
 and the wait had been long and things had been hard,

383
00:16:52,820 --> 00:16:55,580
 but God breaks in.

384
00:16:55,580 --> 00:16:59,340
 And that is the message of Christmas.

385
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:03,300
 And the whole birth of Jesus is God breaking in

386
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:07,340
 to the bleak, dark, coldness of this world

387
00:17:07,340 --> 00:17:10,580
 with new lived hope.

388
00:17:10,580 --> 00:17:12,700
 I wanna invite you to reflect around that idea

389
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:14,460
 of God breaking in.

390
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:17,340
 And we're gonna do that through listening to another carol

391
00:17:17,340 --> 00:17:19,100
 from our worship team.

392
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:21,260
 And they're gonna sing this over us as they do.

393
00:17:21,260 --> 00:17:23,020
 So the lyrics will be on the screen behind.

394
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:26,540
 And I want you to read the lyrics and reflect on the lyrics

395
00:17:26,540 --> 00:17:28,820
 in relation to what I've been teaching with you so far.

396
00:17:28,820 --> 00:17:32,580
 And this beautiful idea that God can break in

397
00:17:32,580 --> 00:17:35,380
 to those moments that seem the bleakest.

398
00:17:35,380 --> 00:17:36,260
 Let's take a look.

399
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:39,020
 (pages rustling)

400
00:17:39,020 --> 00:17:43,540
 (piano notes playing)

401
00:17:43,540 --> 00:17:44,620
 I love that.

402
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:48,220
 Final line or the final stanza of the hymn.

403
00:17:48,220 --> 00:17:50,100
 Let me read it to you one more time.

404
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:52,380
 What can I give him as poor as I am?

405
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:54,420
 If I were a shepherd, I would bring a lamb.

406
00:17:54,420 --> 00:17:55,940
 If I were a wise man, I would do my part.

407
00:17:55,940 --> 00:17:59,700
 Yet what I can give him is I can give him my heart.

408
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:02,020
 Beautiful message of Christmas there.

409
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:04,820
 But I think also leaning into what Luke

410
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:06,820
 is trying to say to us in the passage

411
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:08,620
 we're looking at this morning.

412
00:18:08,620 --> 00:18:10,540
 We are to give Jesus our heart.

413
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:14,620
 The challenge is what heart are you giving him?

414
00:18:14,620 --> 00:18:18,700
 Is it a heart that's big enough to receive all that he is

415
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:22,140
 or a heart so small that you're expecting him

416
00:18:22,140 --> 00:18:24,580
 to reduce himself to you?

417
00:18:24,580 --> 00:18:30,500
 It is this that basically Simeon is filled with

418
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:33,580
 as he speaks out over Israel.

419
00:18:33,580 --> 00:18:36,380
 Let me read to you one more time these words

420
00:18:36,380 --> 00:18:39,060
 that Simeon prophesies over Jesus

421
00:18:39,060 --> 00:18:40,820
 and the people in the temple.

422
00:18:40,820 --> 00:18:43,260
 He says, "Sovereign Lord, as you have promised,

423
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:46,020
 "you can now dismiss your servant in peace.

424
00:18:46,020 --> 00:18:49,340
 "For my eyes have indeed seen your salvation,

425
00:18:49,340 --> 00:18:52,820
 "which you have prepared in the sight of all the people.

426
00:18:52,820 --> 00:18:55,620
 "A light for revelation to the Gentiles

427
00:18:55,620 --> 00:18:59,420
 "and a glory to your people Israel."

428
00:18:59,420 --> 00:19:01,460
 It's beautiful to me that Simeon filled with the spirit

429
00:19:01,460 --> 00:19:04,940
 comes and says something that actually

430
00:19:04,940 --> 00:19:07,380
 the Jewish people were not expecting.

431
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:10,220
 If we step back from the moment

432
00:19:10,220 --> 00:19:12,740
 and just look at the history that leads us to it,

433
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:14,500
 as I said earlier, that there has been

434
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:17,820
 a 400 year waiting period for this moment.

435
00:19:17,820 --> 00:19:20,020
 400 years where the last prophecy

436
00:19:20,020 --> 00:19:21,820
 in Malachi in the Old Testament

437
00:19:21,820 --> 00:19:25,340
 to this moment where Simeon prophesies in the temple.

438
00:19:25,340 --> 00:19:27,500
 That's a long period of time.

439
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,900
 And during that time, the Jewish people

440
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:32,660
 had constructed for themselves this Messiah

441
00:19:32,660 --> 00:19:34,380
 that they were longing to come.

442
00:19:34,380 --> 00:19:36,220
 And they had thought about what is it

443
00:19:36,220 --> 00:19:40,500
 that they want this Messiah to be when he does arrive?

444
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:43,220
 And the three primary focuses for the Jewish people

445
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:45,220
 in the first century as they prayed

446
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:46,860
 and longed for the Messiah were this.

447
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:49,940
 Number one, that when the Messiah comes,

448
00:19:49,940 --> 00:19:52,380
 the Romans will be pushed away.

449
00:19:52,380 --> 00:19:55,900
 The oppression that we're under under the Romans

450
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:59,460
 would finish and the Romans would rule us no more.

451
00:19:59,460 --> 00:20:01,380
 Number two, when the Messiah comes,

452
00:20:01,380 --> 00:20:03,060
 sin will be suddenly dealt with.

453
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:05,380
 It'll be like an apocalyptic moment

454
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:07,500
 where the world will be changed in an instant

455
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,860
 and sin will be no more.

456
00:20:09,860 --> 00:20:13,100
 And when the Messiah comes, we, the Jewish people,

457
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:15,420
 would have our rightful place again,

458
00:20:15,420 --> 00:20:18,620
 ruling here in the world with our right land

459
00:20:18,620 --> 00:20:20,060
 and our right context.

460
00:20:20,060 --> 00:20:24,260
 So this idea of Romans be gone, sin be gone,

461
00:20:24,260 --> 00:20:26,300
 and for us to have a place of power

462
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,860
 and leadership for ourselves, once again,

463
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:33,860
 this was what was wrapped up in the desire for the Messiah.

464
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:36,660
 Now think also, this is the first moment

465
00:20:36,660 --> 00:20:40,940
 that the Messiah is proclaimed publicly in Israel.

466
00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:44,220
 Remember, the angels had come and proclaimed the Messiah

467
00:20:44,220 --> 00:20:46,860
 over the shepherds, and the shepherds had gone

468
00:20:46,860 --> 00:20:50,140
 to see Jesus in the stable.

469
00:20:50,140 --> 00:20:52,100
 The star had shone in the sky,

470
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:55,060
 which enabled the Magi to journey towards Jesus,

471
00:20:55,060 --> 00:20:56,020
 bringing their gifts,

472
00:20:56,020 --> 00:20:59,420
 and able to do that before him in the stable.

473
00:20:59,420 --> 00:21:02,100
 But 40 days later, this is the first time

474
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:05,580
 that God decides to make a public announcement

475
00:21:05,580 --> 00:21:08,660
 about the Messiah and who the Messiah is,

476
00:21:08,660 --> 00:21:11,820
 and he's doing that announcement in the very center

477
00:21:11,820 --> 00:21:15,780
 of what the Jewish culture and religious sort of hub was

478
00:21:15,780 --> 00:21:18,180
 of the day, right there in the temple.

479
00:21:18,220 --> 00:21:21,300
 And notice what God, by his Spirit,

480
00:21:21,300 --> 00:21:24,500
 inspires Simeon to say first.

481
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:27,300
 The first thing that comes out of his mouth is this,

482
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:32,300
 this Messiah is a light of revelation to the Gentiles.

483
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:38,340
 You can almost imagine,

484
00:21:38,340 --> 00:21:41,180
 you could have heard a pin drop in that room.

485
00:21:41,180 --> 00:21:43,020
 This is the temple.

486
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:46,860
 This is the seat of Jewish power.

487
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:48,540
 This is where they've been longing and praying

488
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:50,500
 and hoping for, and there's Simeon,

489
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:51,940
 and the first thing he says is,

490
00:21:51,940 --> 00:21:53,620
 you wanna know who the Messiah is?

491
00:21:53,620 --> 00:21:55,420
 You wanna know what this Jesus is?

492
00:21:55,420 --> 00:21:58,300
 He's gonna be a light of revelation to the Gentiles.

493
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:59,780
 Isn't that great?

494
00:21:59,780 --> 00:22:04,780
 And you can imagine the people standing around him saying,

495
00:22:04,780 --> 00:22:08,020
 whoa, hang on, hang on a sec.

496
00:22:08,020 --> 00:22:12,060
 The Gentiles, the ones who rule over us,

497
00:22:12,060 --> 00:22:14,820
 the ones who are oppressing us,

498
00:22:14,820 --> 00:22:19,380
 this one is going to be a light of revelation to them.

499
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:22,500
 That doesn't sound like grace.

500
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:23,340
 It's funny, isn't it?

501
00:22:23,340 --> 00:22:26,420
 Grace is only ever amazing when it's grace for us.

502
00:22:26,420 --> 00:22:33,100
 When we find out that grace is for our enemy,

503
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:37,620
 for our oppressor, for the one who has enslaved us,

504
00:22:37,620 --> 00:22:39,300
 you're telling me that the Messiah,

505
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,540
 this is the first thing, notice God here.

506
00:22:41,540 --> 00:22:43,660
 This is the first thing that's announced

507
00:22:43,660 --> 00:22:45,980
 to the Jewish power and authority

508
00:22:45,980 --> 00:22:47,780
 and the priests and the people

509
00:22:47,780 --> 00:22:51,940
 that Jesus is gonna be the Messiah that you did not expect.

510
00:22:51,940 --> 00:22:55,100
 You thought the Messiah was gonna push away the Gentiles.

511
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:57,780
 You thought this was all about your re-enthronement.

512
00:22:57,780 --> 00:22:59,180
 No, no, no, the Messiah, yes,

513
00:22:59,180 --> 00:23:00,540
 there's gonna be glory to Israel,

514
00:23:00,540 --> 00:23:01,820
 which is what he says second,

515
00:23:01,820 --> 00:23:03,140
 but the first thing he says is,

516
00:23:03,140 --> 00:23:05,420
 here's what you need to know about Jesus,

517
00:23:05,420 --> 00:23:08,180
 'cause if you don't know this about Jesus, Jewish people,

518
00:23:08,180 --> 00:23:09,820
 you're gonna miss him completely.

519
00:23:09,820 --> 00:23:12,500
 He's coming to show grace and mercy

520
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:15,060
 and love and revelation and bring change

521
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:17,900
 to the ones that you currently hate.

522
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:24,380
 I mean, talk about God breaking open some boxes

523
00:23:24,380 --> 00:23:27,540
 that his people had put Jesus in.

524
00:23:27,540 --> 00:23:30,580
 Oh, it needs to look like this.

525
00:23:30,580 --> 00:23:34,620
 God says, the first thing you need to know,

526
00:23:34,620 --> 00:23:36,460
 it isn't, it's gonna look nothing

527
00:23:36,460 --> 00:23:39,220
 like you thought it was gonna look.

528
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:42,300
 And if you don't realize it now,

529
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:45,260
 you're gonna completely miss out.

530
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:49,940
 It's interesting 'cause Jesus then in his ministry,

531
00:23:49,940 --> 00:23:51,700
 as he begins to inaugurate the kingdom of God

532
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:54,220
 and as he begins to show that through the miracles he does,

533
00:23:54,220 --> 00:23:56,580
 as he begins to do that through the teaching that he does,

534
00:23:56,580 --> 00:23:59,100
 often in parables, he would end those teachings saying,

535
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:00,980
 if you have ears to hear, let him hear.

536
00:24:00,980 --> 00:24:03,220
 If you can see with eyes, let you see.

537
00:24:03,220 --> 00:24:05,580
 In other words, I am here, I'm the Messiah.

538
00:24:05,580 --> 00:24:07,060
 I'm the fullness of what you've ever had,

539
00:24:07,060 --> 00:24:09,820
 but it looks different to the thing

540
00:24:09,820 --> 00:24:11,500
 that you have created me for.

541
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:14,820
 And unless you are enabled to expand what you thought

542
00:24:14,820 --> 00:24:17,500
 and embrace the new, you're gonna completely miss out.

543
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:20,380
 This is why Jesus, when he's standing over Jerusalem

544
00:24:20,380 --> 00:24:23,780
 at the end of his ministry and the triumphal entry,

545
00:24:23,780 --> 00:24:26,660
 looking over the temple as well up on the hill,

546
00:24:26,660 --> 00:24:29,660
 he says in the final five days of his life,

547
00:24:29,660 --> 00:24:31,660
 he's looking at that temple and he says this.

548
00:24:31,660 --> 00:24:34,460
 He says, if only you knew who it was

549
00:24:34,460 --> 00:24:36,060
 that was coming to you now,

550
00:24:36,060 --> 00:24:37,660
 the Prince of Peace coming to you,

551
00:24:37,660 --> 00:24:39,420
 but he says, it is hidden from you.

552
00:24:39,420 --> 00:24:45,940
 You put me in a box and you're refusing to accept me

553
00:24:45,940 --> 00:24:47,980
 if I don't fit into your box.

554
00:24:47,980 --> 00:24:48,820
 But guess what?

555
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:50,340
 It's not about me fitting into your box,

556
00:24:50,340 --> 00:24:53,160
 it's about your box getting smashed.

557
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:58,340
 This is the prophetic word to Israel

558
00:24:58,340 --> 00:25:01,420
 right at the inauguration of Jesus' dedication

559
00:25:01,420 --> 00:25:02,500
 in the temple.

560
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:06,940
 Your box that you have placed me in,

561
00:25:06,940 --> 00:25:11,940
 if you do not smash that box, you will miss out.

562
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:16,100
 In other words, it was almost like God was saying,

563
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:19,020
 you are not prepared, Israel,

564
00:25:19,020 --> 00:25:22,660
 for the receiving of the Messiah.

565
00:25:22,660 --> 00:25:24,860
 And I'm bringing a prophetic word through Simeon

566
00:25:24,860 --> 00:25:29,020
 to you right now, that if you can hear it,

567
00:25:29,020 --> 00:25:31,480
 if you can open your heart to it,

568
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:33,380
 you will see Jesus bigger.

569
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:36,700
 You will see your Messiah far bigger and far grander

570
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:38,500
 than you could ever see him.

571
00:25:38,500 --> 00:25:42,700
 He is more glorious, more powerful, more saving,

572
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:45,540
 more loving, more graceful, more merciful

573
00:25:45,540 --> 00:25:47,540
 than you had ever thought he was.

574
00:25:47,540 --> 00:25:50,540
 He is gonna be an even greater glory to Israel

575
00:25:50,540 --> 00:25:54,860
 if you would just let him out of your box.

576
00:25:54,860 --> 00:25:58,220
 It's like he's kind of wanting to take a hammer.

577
00:25:58,220 --> 00:25:59,060
 I'm gonna do this for you.

578
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:01,340
 I'm gonna move this out of the way.

579
00:26:01,340 --> 00:26:04,060
 It's like he wants to take a hammer to this box

580
00:26:04,060 --> 00:26:05,900
 and do this, you ready?

581
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:06,740
 No, I'm not gonna do that.

582
00:26:06,740 --> 00:26:07,560
 It's my wife's.

583
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:10,580
 (congregation laughing)

584
00:26:10,580 --> 00:26:12,940
 This is my wife's jewelry box, okay?

585
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:14,540
 She's currently on holiday in New Zealand.

586
00:26:14,540 --> 00:26:17,380
 She would be very upset if I smashed her jewelry box.

587
00:26:17,380 --> 00:26:22,380
 But that's, it's like you need glasses in the front row.

588
00:26:22,380 --> 00:26:25,700
 But that's essentially what God is doing

589
00:26:25,700 --> 00:26:28,580
 through Simeon to Israel in this moment.

590
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:32,700
 And I wanna say a couple of things to us today

591
00:26:32,700 --> 00:26:34,740
 in connection to that.

592
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:36,820
 Number one, I don't think it's just Israel

593
00:26:36,820 --> 00:26:38,220
 that puts Jesus in a box.

594
00:26:38,220 --> 00:26:41,660
 I think we all have the tendency to do it.

595
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:45,100
 Number two, in the same way that I think Simeon

596
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:47,700
 was this prophetic declaration to Israel,

597
00:26:47,700 --> 00:26:50,980
 you are not yet prepared for the Messiah that is coming.

598
00:26:50,980 --> 00:26:53,780
 And if you don't get ready, you're gonna miss.

599
00:26:53,780 --> 00:26:55,780
 I wanna say this boldly to some of you in this room,

600
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:57,240
 and this will resonate with some of you.

601
00:26:57,240 --> 00:27:02,160
 You are not yet prepared for the Jesus of 2026 in your life.

602
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:05,480
 And you need to break him out of the box

603
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:07,140
 you've placed him in.

604
00:27:07,140 --> 00:27:09,340
 Otherwise, you will miss out on all the things

605
00:27:09,340 --> 00:27:11,580
 that he might have for you in 2026.

606
00:27:11,580 --> 00:27:17,900
 You see, we place Jesus in boxes all the time in our life.

607
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:20,860
 I think we have the box of limitations

608
00:27:20,860 --> 00:27:23,700
 where we limit the power of Jesus down.

609
00:27:23,700 --> 00:27:25,100
 And we say, I don't think Jesus

610
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:26,740
 could touch that part of my life.

611
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:29,080
 I don't think he could heal me of that.

612
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:32,000
 I don't think he could address that situation in my life.

613
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,760
 It's been a long time, nothing's ever happened.

614
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:35,360
 I just don't think he can do it.

615
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:37,200
 Boxes of limitations.

616
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:40,600
 We have boxes of experience.

617
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:42,520
 Well, Jesus has never done that for me.

618
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:43,600
 Oh, he might have done that for you.

619
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:44,520
 That's good, that's nice.

620
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:47,260
 That's your testimony, but that's not my experience.

621
00:27:47,260 --> 00:27:50,040
 And we limit the power of Jesus in our lives

622
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:54,260
 and we place him in a box because of our experience of him.

623
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:57,240
 I think we have boxes of culture.

624
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:59,480
 Oh, this is how I do things.

625
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:01,200
 This is how my people do things.

626
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:03,140
 This is the way of our culture.

627
00:28:03,140 --> 00:28:05,460
 And Jesus doesn't fit to that culture.

628
00:28:05,460 --> 00:28:07,620
 And I think we need to shift Jesus

629
00:28:07,620 --> 00:28:09,980
 and make him look a little bit more like us

630
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:13,320
 rather than make myself look more like him.

631
00:28:13,320 --> 00:28:15,600
 And Jesus comes and gives us the culture

632
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:17,320
 of the kingdom of God,

633
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:18,900
 one that can be seen and flourishing

634
00:28:18,900 --> 00:28:20,480
 in all cultures in this world,

635
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:23,720
 but one that needs to be a new culture for each one.

636
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,920
 Or perhaps we have boxes of theology.

637
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:27,860
 Ooh, yeah.

638
00:28:27,860 --> 00:28:30,160
 Oh, this is how I know Jesus is.

639
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:31,200
 I mean, I've read the scriptures.

640
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,060
 This is it.

641
00:28:32,060 --> 00:28:32,900
 I know it.

642
00:28:32,900 --> 00:28:33,720
 It's like this.

643
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:34,560
 It's a tight little thing like this.

644
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:38,040
 And sometimes our theological boxes

645
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:40,860
 can actually contain him down

646
00:28:40,860 --> 00:28:44,860
 rather than keep him mysterious and marvelous and amazing.

647
00:28:44,860 --> 00:28:49,360
 Simeon speaks out a bold word to his people.

648
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:52,040
 He's gonna be the light of revelation to the Gentiles.

649
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:54,480
 You need to open your box, he's saying.

650
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:56,440
 Smash it, change it.

651
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:58,400
 Jesus is different.

652
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,820
 This is why Paul, when he writes to the church in Ephesus,

653
00:29:00,820 --> 00:29:03,560
 chapter three, says, "Jesus," this one,

654
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:05,640
 "is able to do immeasurably more

655
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:08,280
 "than you could ever ask or imagine."

656
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:10,520
 Don't limit him down.

657
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:11,760
 He can do immeasurably more.

658
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:14,060
 "So that his glory would be seen in Christ Jesus

659
00:29:14,060 --> 00:29:16,300
 "and in the church," he says.

660
00:29:16,300 --> 00:29:20,360
 And there's Jesus himself ministering to the people,

661
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:22,320
 constantly challenging the boxes

662
00:29:22,320 --> 00:29:24,320
 that they place the Messiah in,

663
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:27,560
 constantly challenging the old traditions and laws

664
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:28,960
 that have hemmed him in,

665
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:31,520
 and constantly standing before the people and saying,

666
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:32,760
 "I'm with you now.

667
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,880
 "Come and see and taste.

668
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:37,500
 "All of you who are weary and burdened, come to me,

669
00:29:37,500 --> 00:29:38,880
 "and I will give you rest.

670
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:42,380
 "I am bigger and more grander and more powerful

671
00:29:42,380 --> 00:29:45,000
 "than you have created the box for me to be."

672
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,480
 Smash your box.

673
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:50,660
 And I can't think of a more important word

674
00:29:50,660 --> 00:29:54,300
 as we finish 2025 and as we move into 2026.

675
00:29:54,300 --> 00:29:56,520
 That God would stand over you today,

676
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:59,600
 maybe with the same prophetic utterance,

677
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:02,640
 and say, "You've placed me too much in a box.

678
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:05,680
 "I am far bigger than how you currently see me.

679
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:08,000
 "Are you willing to open your eyes?

680
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:11,280
 "For those who have eyes, let them see,

681
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:14,400
 "and those who have ears, let them hear."

682
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:16,800
 Can I pray for you?

683
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:17,640
 Let's pray.

684
00:30:20,580 --> 00:30:24,560
 Father, we are humbled by this beautiful part

685
00:30:24,560 --> 00:30:25,740
 of the Christmas story,

686
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:30,220
 where the very first utterance publicly over Israel

687
00:30:30,220 --> 00:30:33,520
 is to say this Savior is the Savior for the ones

688
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:35,700
 that you do not want to have a Savior.

689
00:30:35,700 --> 00:30:40,760
 This Messiah is big enough to offer love and mercy

690
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:44,420
 and forgiveness to even those who you consider your enemies.

691
00:30:44,420 --> 00:30:48,980
 The grace is so much bigger than you thought.

692
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:53,060
 And Father, I wanna pray for each of us

693
00:30:53,060 --> 00:30:57,920
 as we finish off 2025 and prepare ourselves for 2026.

694
00:30:57,920 --> 00:31:01,480
 As this week on Wednesday and Thursday,

695
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,580
 we celebrate the arrival of Jesus.

696
00:31:03,580 --> 00:31:06,860
 Lord, we wanna go into that process

697
00:31:06,860 --> 00:31:09,460
 aware of the boxes that we've placed you in,

698
00:31:09,460 --> 00:31:13,720
 where we've limited you because of our experience

699
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:16,320
 or our culture or our theology,

700
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:19,000
 because we try to sort you out

701
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:22,000
 and create a nice, neat little box for you to fit in.

702
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:26,460
 And Lord, I do believe that there are people in this room

703
00:31:26,460 --> 00:31:31,180
 who are not yet prepared for the incredible things

704
00:31:31,180 --> 00:31:33,720
 that you want to do in their lives in the year ahead.

705
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:36,560
 And you're saying, "Would you smash the box?

706
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:39,600
 "Would you open your heart more?

707
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:42,480
 "Would you not be so skeptical?

708
00:31:42,480 --> 00:31:46,760
 "Would you believe that I am grander and bigger

709
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:50,440
 "than you've ever thought, that I am immeasurably more

710
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:52,600
 "than you could ever ask or imagine?

711
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,940
 "And I am that for you.

712
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:58,400
 "And this is not about you changing me

713
00:31:58,400 --> 00:32:00,000
 "to fit your comfortable life.

714
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:03,600
 "It's about me challenging you to change you

715
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:05,760
 "to walk into the best life."

716
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:10,100
 So Holy Spirit, I wanna pray for anyone in this room

717
00:32:10,100 --> 00:32:12,260
 where this message is resonating with them.

718
00:32:12,260 --> 00:32:15,480
 As we're in this transition time

719
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:17,080
 between one year to the next,

720
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:20,880
 Father, as a church community, we want to move, Lord,

721
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:28,000
 into the year with no more boxes, no more limitations,

722
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:32,060
 nothing limited by experience or culture or theology,

723
00:32:32,060 --> 00:32:37,060
 but an openness in spirit and heart for more of you.

724
00:32:37,060 --> 00:32:43,240
 Would you be a light of revelation to us,

725
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,680
 the Gentiles in this room?

726
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:47,440
 (gentle music)

727
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:49,600
 Would you reveal yourself in grander and bigger ways

728
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:51,200
 than we could ever have imagined?

729
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:54,960
 And may our worship of you expand

730
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:59,400
 beyond what my heart currently says about you.

731
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:01,400
 Would you show me things about you

732
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:05,400
 that would set my heart on fire, Lord?

733
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:12,040
 I am not satisfied with the Jesus I currently know,

734
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:14,380
 as grateful as I am for it.

735
00:33:14,380 --> 00:33:16,340
 Would you be more, Lord?

736
00:33:16,340 --> 00:33:23,200
 Would you open me to fresh wind, new wine?

737
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:26,920
 Would you make in me a new wineskin?

738
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:30,060
 And would it be for your glory?

739
00:33:30,060 --> 00:33:32,560
 We pray this in Jesus' name.

740
00:33:32,560 --> 00:33:36,480
 Everyone says, would you stand with me?

741
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:39,680
 And we're gonna respond together as a community in worship.

742
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:42,260
 (gentle music)

